								<div class="title" id="post-title-3718369">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/shaggydredlocks" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1722371); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1722371&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610236584" alt="Shaggydredlocks" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1722371)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/shaggydredlocks" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1722371); return false;" >Shaggydredlocks</a></span> <span class="odate time_1519279159 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">22 Feb 2018 05:59</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3718369">
									

<p>There are a quite a few elements at play here I've seen on-and-off throughout the wiki. In a less capable author's hands, this cold have wound up being trite. It did follow some typical beats, but goddamn does it stay entertaining throughout, and is one of the more compelling takes of pitting the EC against the O5.</p>
<p>The aic-interaction was a fresh framing device that's used to great effect here, and is something I've been waiting to see since I came across the Skynet MTF. +1!</p>

							</div>

								
					
