    <div class="post-container" id="fpc-3718377">
                      
		<div class="post" id="post-3718377">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,3718377)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-3718377">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser deleted" data-id="3122708"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/common--images/avatars/default/a16.png" alt=""/>(account deleted)</span> <span class="odate time_1519279592 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">22 Feb 2018 06:06</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3718377">
									

<p>No-voting &#8212; this was a hard one for me. On one hand, I love the fundamental anomaly (the notion of physically personifying a concept, then having actions taken against that person impact the concept itself). There's a lot of bits here I also really liked &#8212; the idea of the Ethics Committee equivalent of the Red Hand, the casual mention of members of the O5 council being shot in the head and 'not dead' &#8212; etc.</p>
<p>On the other hand&#8230;</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">FEEDBACK</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<ul>
<li>The final interview between the Administrator and the 001 fell rather flat for me; it gave me a strong vibe of 'trying to feel profound'.</li>
<li>On one hand, I kind of like the hypocrisy of the O5 council (I liked how the note mentioned expanding 001's effect to others, then we discover that they've selected no one to expand it to). On the other hand, I kind of don't &#8212; this reduces the O5 council to the Injustice League. I think a more compelling story here would have been something involving a few (or even just one) O5s abusing the anomaly.</li>
<li>The AI stuff was kind of cute, but also didn't work for me. I couldn't figure out what their dialogue really added, on the whole. I feel like the story could have been communicated much more cleanly and effectively as an epistolary piece (via emails, perhaps).</li>
<li>Finally, I feel very much like this fits as more of a story/tale than an 001. I'm sure you're going to get a lot of that (and I'm sure you were expecting it); in a sense, this is in the same boat as When Day Breaks &#8212; but while I feel When Day Breaks works as an 001, I feel as if this doesn't. It's hard for me to pin down precisely why &#8212; I think certain elements of the piece just didn't hook me. It might just be that my standards for 001s are <em>much</em> higher than my standards for tales.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>Regardless, at the very least, I enjoyed the writing in this piece and several of the ideas you presented. It seems like I might be (mostly) alone on feeling like this doesn't work as an 001 (which is quite fine; different tastes and aesthetics, after all). Good luck with it!</p>

							</div>

								
					
