<p>(Thanks!)</p>
<p>And yeah, I mean &#8212; my issue isn't that this fails to present the Foundation sympathetically; I think the Foundation is a pretty scary, authoritarian organization that reflects a lot of the real life organizations you mentioned. My issue is more that in a room of 12 people from various backgrounds, I don't expect all 12 of them to be okay with this.</p>
<p>Like, this might have worked better for me if it was told from the perspective of 2 or 3 O5 members who had dissented over this issue and now felt the need to take the council down. Or if it was demonstrated that not all the O5s had taken advantage of this immortality &#8212; or heck, just if what initiated this whole thing was a member of the council secretly forwarding the SCP file to the Ethics Committee.</p>

